<b>4.</b> Billy took a math test yesterday. Billy had to answer this problem&colon;
<br></br>
<br>John went to the store every week for 6 weeks to buy grocery's for his family. His budget every week was &dollar;150. If spent &dollar;147, &dollar;143, &dollar;152, &dollar;146, &dollar;139, and &dollar;141 each week. His mom said if he watched the sales, he could keep the extra money to sve up for a bike. How much did John save up?</br>
<br></br>
Billy &times; each week by 6, added them together, then &minus; 150. He got &dollar;5058! What did Billy do wrong? Find the correct answer.
